================================================================
  RQ2: Device Cache Directory Sizing Experiment
  Measures directory pressure vs working set size
================================================================

  Using CXL GPU device 0
  Device initialized.  Running experiments...
  Trials per config: 10
  BFS sizes: 100, 500, 1000, 2000, 5000, 10000, 20000, 50000
  B-tree sizes: 100, 500, 1000, 5000, 10000, 50000

================================================================
  Experiment 4: Hardware directory size (BAR2 registers)
================================================================

  Directory size (from stats):  13 entries
  Register offsets:
    CXL_GPU_REG_COH_DIR_SIZE  = 0x0318
    CXL_GPU_REG_COH_DIR_USED  = 0x0320

  Note: hardware directory size is fixed.  To study the effect of
  directory capacity, we vary the working set size instead.
  When working set > directory capacity, evictions and snoop misses
  increase, revealing the capacity cliff.

================================================================
  Experiment 1: Graph BFS directory pressure sweep
================================================================
  Varying N to create different working set sizes.
  Each node = 64 bytes (1 cache line), ER graph, avg degree 6.
  10 trials per configuration, reporting median.

